# Part 05 – HTML Forms

- In this part, I am learning about **HTML Forms**.  
- Forms are used to **collect input from users**, such as names, emails, passwords, feedback, or any other data.  
- They are essential for interactive websites and web applications.

---

## What Is an HTML Form?

An HTML form is a container for different input elements that allow users to submit information to a server.  

The basic form structure looks like this:

```html
<form action="submit.html" method="post">
  <!-- Input fields go here -->
</form>
```

### Explanation:
- `<form>` → Defines the form container
- `action` → The page or script that will process the form data
- `method` → How data is sent: `post` or `get`

---

## Common Form Elements

### 1. Text Input

```html
<label>Name:</label><br>
<input type="text" name="name"><br><br>
```

- `type="text"` → Accepts plain text input
- `<label>` → Describes the input field

---

### 2. Email Input

```html
<label>Email:</label><br>
<input type="email" name="email"><br><br>
```

- `type="email"` → Accepts only valid email addresses

---

### 3. Password Input

```html
<label>Password:</label><br>
<input type="password" name="password"><br><br>
```

- `type="password"` → Masks the input for privacy

---

### 4. Submit Button

```html
<input type="submit" value="Submit">
```

- Sends the form data to the server when clicked

---

## Complete Simple Form Example

```html
<form action="submit.html" method="post">
  <label>Name:</label><br>
  <input type="text" name="name"><br><br>

  <label>Email:</label><br>
  <input type="email" name="email"><br><br>

  <label>Password:</label><br>
  <input type="password" name="password"><br><br>

  <input type="submit" value="Submit">
</form>
```

---

## Why HTML Forms Are Important

- Forms allow websites to interact with users
- Collect user feedback, registration details, or login information
- Essential for dynamic and interactive web applications

---

## Learning Summary

In Part 05, I learned how to:
- Create HTML forms using the `<form>` tag
- Add text, email, and password inputs
- Add a submit button to send data

HTML forms are fundamental for building interactive websites.
